      "content": "<p>Is this considered acceptable in dynamic programming? For example, if you have a counter, or something such as &#34;you can use no more than n items&#34;, it seems excessive to make an entire table storing that, when you can simply just decrement it.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Can you do something like T(i) = T(i -1) and n = n - 1 where n &gt; 0?</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>If not, is the only option to make another dimension in the table and drag along n?</p>", 
